From solymos at ualberta.ca  Tue Jun 12 18:11:41 2012
From: solymos at ualberta.ca (Peter Solymos)
Date: Tue, 12 Jun 2012 10:11:41 -0600
Subject: [R-sig-eco] How to transform a cross-tabulated matrix (as
 provided by mefa4::Xtab) for further multivariate analyses
In-Reply-To: <CAAVnHstk6d9b5BR8fTYorjLpd++LYQKdbY1qx7UqUrwN84Zzow@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAAVnHstk6d9b5BR8fTYorjLpd++LYQKdbY1qx7UqUrwN84Zzow@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <CAH9coKaifRRBuy_KE+0SUPV1zYZAP4Nth_HiypzC58WCoq38=Q@mail.gmail.com>

Ivailo,

Some (but not all) vegan functions internally coerce the "matrix like"
input object to matrix using 'x <- as.matrix(x)'. The as.matrix()
coercion method is defined for sparse matrices in the Matrix package,
and that is why it works for some (but not all) vegan functions. In
case it does not happen I'd recommend using the 'x <- as.matrix(x)'
coercion prior to supplying the data to a vegan function.

Cheers,

Peter

